{"type":"message","id":"216cd4e5","parentId":"05d1d5c1","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:51:20.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me implement the fixes. I'll focus on two main fixes:\n\n1. **Modify `cmd_wait_login`** to detect QR expiration and refresh the QR automatically, informing the user.\n\n2. **Write a new version of `update_xhs_web_session.sh`** that properly waits for login instead of exiting immediately.\n\nLet me start with the `cmd_wait_login` fix in `cli.py`. I need to modify it to:\n1. Check if the page still shows a QR code (vs. some other state)\n2. If the QR has changed, fetch and display the new QR URL\n3. This requires modifying the `wait_for_login` function in `login.py` or the `cmd_wait_login` in `cli.py`\n\n\n4. The core issue is that when `wait-login` reconnects to the saved tab, the QR code might have expired and the page has refreshed, so I need to detect when we're still on a QR page and surface the new one to the user\n\nI'll create a modified `cmd_wait_login` that polls for login status while also monitoring for QR code changes, fetching fresh QR data when the page appears to be on a login screen.\n\nActually, I should step back and think about this more practically. The user needs to see the browser window with the QR code so they can actually scan it, and the current approach of creating a fresh tab without the user's existing session means they're always getting a new QR code. Maybe the simpler fix is to just make sure the Chrome window is visible and stable long enough for the user to complete the login flow. Let me implement the fixes: modify `wait_for_login` in login.py to detect and report QR refresh, update `cmd_wait_login` in cli.py to surface this information, and revise `update_xhs_web_session.sh` to wait for login instead of timing out.","thinkingSignature":"ba0252e04c824642bd50fd0df26007c1327f2c22eae6b68319d7e0fbb5aee738"},{"type":"text","text":"现在实施修复。先修改 `login.py` 的 `wait_for_login`，加入 QR 过期检测和刷新通知：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1er075w3fzv5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":240,"limit":50,"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/xiaohongshu-skills/scripts/xhs/login.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42777,"output":470,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68124,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773971467399}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d4fc5ec","parentId":"216cd4e5","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:51:20.071Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1er075w3fzv5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        page: CDP 页面对象。\n        phone: 手机号（不含国家码，如 13800138000）。\n\n    Returns:\n        True 验证码已发送，False 已登录（无需再登录）。\n\n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: 找不到登录表单或手机号输入框。\n    \"\"\"\n    # 如果当前页面已在 explore，跳过重复导航\n    current_url = page.evaluate(\"location.href\") or \"\"\n    if \"explore\" not in current_url:\n        page.navigate(EXPLORE_URL)\n        page.wait_for_load()\n\n    # 直接等待登录容器出现（合并了 _wait_for_auth_ui 的逻辑，避免重复等待）\n    try:\n        page.wait_for_element(LOGIN_CONTAINER, timeout=10.0)\n    except Exception as exc:\n        # 可能已登录（没有登录容器），检查登录状态\n        if page.has_element(LOGIN_STATUS):\n            return False\n        raise RuntimeError(\"找不到登录表单\") from exc\n\n    if page.has_element(LOGIN_STATUS):\n        return False\n\n    sleep_random(200, 400)\n\n    # 点击手机号输入框并逐字输入\n    page.click_element(PHONE_INPUT)\n    sleep_random(200, 400)\n    page.type_text(phone, delay_ms=80)\n    sleep_random(200, 400)\n\n    # 先勾选用户协议，再点获取验证码\n    if not page.has_element(AGREE_CHECKBOX_CHECKED):\n        page.click_element(AGREE_CHECKBOX)\n        sleep_random(300, 600)\n\n    # 点击\"获取验证码\"\n    page.click_element(GET_CODE_BUTTON)\n\n    # 事件驱动：轮询按钮文字直到出现倒计时数字，替代固定 2-2.5s 等待\n    _wait_for_countdown(page)\n\n    logger.info(\"验证码已发送至 %s\", phone[:3] + \"****\" + phone[-4:])\n    return True\n\n\n\n[89 more lines in file. Use offset=290 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773971480053}}
{"type":"message","id":"095162da","parentId":"7d4fc5ec","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:51:23.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me see the full `wait_for_login` function to understand what I need to modify.","thinkingSignature":"8c7dc2aa8917aa565979ed358a5dbe81491ba84a4563a44ad38e8cf74f6f2349"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x9nx4vn2r48u_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":290,"limit":50,"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/xiaohongshu-skills/scripts/xhs/login.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43671,"output":89,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773971480072}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f3cb0d6","parentId":"095162da","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:51:23.838Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x9nx4vn2r48u_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def submit_phone_code(page: Page, code: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"填写短信验证码并提交登录。\n\n    Args:\n        page: CDP 页面对象。\n        code: 收到的短信验证码。\n\n    Returns:\n        True 登录成功，False 失败（超时或验证码错误）。\n    \"\"\"\n    # 点击验证码输入框，先清空再用 CDP 键盘事件逐字输入（isTrusted=true，React 能识别）\n    page.click_element(CODE_INPUT)\n    sleep_random(100, 200)\n    page.evaluate(\n        f\"\"\"(() => {{\n            const el = document.querySelector({json.dumps(CODE_INPUT)});\n            if (el && el.value) {{\n                const setter = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(\n                    window.HTMLInputElement.prototype, 'value'\n                ).set;\n                setter.call(el, '');\n                el.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', {{ bubbles: true }}));\n            }}\n        }})()\"\"\"\n    )\n    page.type_text(code, delay_ms=0)\n    sleep_random(100, 200)\n\n    # 点击登录按钮\n    page.click_element(PHONE_LOGIN_SUBMIT)\n    sleep_random(500, 1000)\n\n    # 检查是否有错误提示\n    err = page.get_element_text(LOGIN_ERR_MSG)\n    if err and err.strip():\n        logger.warning(\"登录失败: %s\", err.strip())\n        return False\n\n    return wait_for_login(page, timeout=30.0)\n\n\ndef logout(page: Page) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"通过页面 UI 退出登录（点击\"更多\"→\"退出登录\"）。\n\n    Args:\n        page: CDP 页面对象。\n\n    Returns:\n        True 退出成功，False 未登录或操作失败。\n    \"\"\"\n\n[39 more lines in file. Use offset=340 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773971483824}}
{"type":"message","id":"8d2bec9a","parentId":"7f3cb0d6","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:51:59.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to modify `wait_for_login` to:\n1. Track the QR code content (b64 data URL) \n2. If the page is still on a QR login page after some time, check if the QR has changed\n3. If the QR has changed, signal to the caller that a refresh is needed\n\nBut modifying `wait_for_login` might break other callers. Let me create a new version or add an optional callback.\n\nActually, a cleaner approach is to add a `on_qr_refresh` callback to `wait_for_login` that gets called when the QR code changes. This way, the CLI can display a message to the user.\n\nOr even simpler: I'll modify `wait_for_login` to return a tuple `(success, qr_refreshed, new_qr_url)` where:\n\n\n- `success`: whether login succeeded\n- `qr_refreshed`: whether the QR was refreshed (expired and new one generated)\n- `new_qr_url`: the new QR URL if refreshed\n\nThis is a clean API change. Let me implement this by having `wait_for_login` capture the initial QR b64 data on the first call, then check on each poll whether it's changed. If the QR has been refreshed, I'll fetch the new one and return the updated URL so the caller can notify the user.\n\nActually, I'm overcomplicating this. A simpler approach would be to add an optional callback parameter to `wait_for_login` that fires when the QR refreshes, or just have `cmd_wait_login` check the page state separately after the initial wait completes. The real issue is that小红书 might refresh the QR code during the login flow, and I need to detect and surface that to the user. I'll modify `wait_for_login` to track QR changes and return the information so the CLI can display a refresh message. I'm settling on a simpler approach: have `wait_for_login` periodically check if the QR code has changed by capturing its state at the start and comparing it each cycle, then returning a signal when it's been refreshed so the CLI can prompt the user to refresh their view. The key insight is that when the QR page refreshes, a new `fetch_qrcode` call will get the updated QR URL, so I just need to detect that transition and surface it to the user with clear instructions to re-scan. Now I'm mapping out the implementation approach: I'll add a `qr_data_url` parameter to `wait_for_login` that captures the initial QR code state, then compare against it on each poll to detect when the page refreshes. When a refresh is detected, I'll fetch the new QR and return it along with a flag so the CLI can surface the update to the user.\n\nModifying wait_for_login to track QR state...","thinkingSignature":"bfda27402c6fd9b5886ae24a6e1683985d65d3d401126fb5cd773016280d6bd7"},{"type":"text","text":"现在修改 `login.py` 的 `wait_for_login`，加入 QR 刷新检测：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zeoxp0258ajc_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/xiaohongshu-skills/scripts/xhs/login.py","oldText":"def wait_for_login(page: Page, timeout: float = 120.0) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"等待扫码登录完成。\n\n    Args:\n        page: CDP 页面对象。\n        timeout: 超时时间（秒）。\n\n    Returns:\n        True 登录成功，False 超时。\n    \"\"\"\n    deadline = time.monotonic() + timeout\n    while time.monotonic() < deadline:\n        if page.has_element(LOGIN_STATUS):\n            logger.info(\"登录成功\")\n            return True\n        time.sleep(0.3)\n    return False","newText":"def wait_for_login(\n    page: Page,\n    timeout: float = 120.0,\n    initial_qr_data_url: str | None = None,\n) -> tuple[bool, str | None]:\n    \"\"\"等待扫码登录完成。\n\n    Args:\n        page: CDP 页面对象。\n        timeout: 超时时间（秒）。\n        initial_qr_data_url: 初始 QR 码的 data URL（用于检测 QR 刷新）。\n\n    Returns:\n        (success, new_qr_data_url):\n        - success=True: 登录成功，new_qr_data_url=None\n        - success=False, new_qr_data_url=新QR的URL: QR 已刷新（用户需重新扫码）\n        - success=False, new_qr_data_url=None: 超时（未检测到 QR 刷新）\n    \"\"\"\n    QR_IMG_SELECTOR = QRCODE_IMG  # Use the selector imported at top of file\n\n    def get_current_qr_data_url() -> str | None:\n        \"\"\"获取当前页面的 QR 码 data URL（精确比较用）。\"\"\"\n        try:\n            src = page.evaluate(\n                f\"document.querySelector({json.dumps(QR_IMG_SELECTOR)})?.src || ''\"\n            )\n            if src and \"base64,\" in src:\n                return src\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        return None\n\n    last_qr_url = initial_qr_data_url\n    deadline = time.monotonic() + timeout\n    while time.monotonic() < deadline:\n        if page.has_element(LOGIN_STATUS):\n            logger.info(\"登录成功\")\n            return True, None\n\n        # 每 10 秒检查一次 QR 是否已刷新（小红书 QR 约 60 秒过期，\n        # 用 10 秒间隔在过期前有充足缓冲，且不会过度查询 DOM）\n        if last_qr_url is not None and int(time.monotonic() * 10) % 10 == 0:\n            current_qr = get_current_qr_data_url()\n            if current_qr and current_qr != last_qr_url:\n                logger.info(\"检测到 QR 码已刷新，需要用户重新扫码\")\n                return False, current_qr\n\n        time.sleep(0.3)\n\n    # 超时：最后一次检查 QR 是否刷新了\n    if last_qr_url is not None:\n        final_qr = get_current_qr_data_url()\n        if final_qr and final_qr != last_qr_url:\n            return False, final_qr\n\n    return False, None"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44147,"output":1284,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70308,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773971483839}}
