{"type":"message","id":"68c5216a","parentId":"d9723268","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:57:11.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files were last modified at 18:10 on March 19. That means the morning_scan.py runs at 9:00 AM but doesn't update these index files. The index files were updated by fetch_data.py on March 19 at 18:10 (after market close).\n\nBut today (March 20), morning_scan.py ran but apparently didn't call fetch_data.py to update the index data. This means:\n\n1. The index data for today hasn't been written\n2. The `latest_index_return_pct()` function reads the last row of the CSV, which is still from yesterday (20260319)\n3. Since yesterday was a down day for 中证2000 (-2.31%), the system incorrectly thinks today is a down day\n\n\n4. The real problem is that morning_scan.py isn't invoking fetch_data.py at all—it's only pulling real-time quotes via akshare, not historical daily data. The index CSVs should be updated after each trading day closes, but today's morning run skipped that step entirely.\n\nLooking at the crontab, the updates happen at 18:10 after market close on March 19, so there's no scheduled task to refresh index data before the 9:00 AM market open on March 20. I need to either add that capability to morning_scan.py or create a dedicated pre-market script to handle it.\n\nThe issue is that `latest_index_return_pct()` reads the last available row without verifying the date, so it would pull yesterday's data even if today's hasn't been written yet. Let me examine the actual function to see how to fix this.","thinkingSignature":"009e5e8ad216003947b0fa7ce66b6e905f0a13ef417f2787a5171ec508b3d633"},{"type":"text","text":"\n文件最后更新是昨天（03-19 18:10），今天09:00的morning_scan没有更新指数文件。让我看看 `latest_index_return_pct` 的防护逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wafkabxmgt8h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd, sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts')\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom run_premarket_risk_v2 import latest_index_return_pct, INDEX_FILES, DATA_ROOT\nprint('DATA_ROOT:', DATA_ROOT)\nimport os\nprint('Exists:', DATA_ROOT.exists())\nprint('Files:', list(DATA_ROOT.glob('index_*_SH.csv'))[:3])\np = DATA_ROOT / 'index_000852_SH.csv'\nprint('Last row:')\ndf = pd.read_csv(p)\nprint(df.iloc[-1][['trade_date','close','pct_chg']].to_dict())\nprint('Return:', latest_index_return_pct(p))\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50985,"output":561,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76423,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773971816547}}
