{"type":"message","id":"5dc7b7a0","parentId":"f9b1221f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:58:05.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix works. Now instead of returning -2.31% (yesterday's data), it returns 0.0 and logs a warning that the data is stale.\n\nNow I need to make the morning scan actually update the index data. Let me check if there's a way to get today's index data in the morning. The issue is that the index data from Tushare is end-of-day data, so it can only be obtained AFTER the market closes. In the morning, we can't get today's index data until after 15:00 of the previous day.\n\nSo the fix I made (returning 0.0 when data is stale) is actually correct for the morning scenario. But we need the data from yesterday close to work with. \n\nThe real problem is that yesterday's index return shouldn't be fed into today's risk calculations as if it were today's performance. For morning precheck, I should either suppress the index return gate entirely or pull real-time data during market hours instead of relying on the previous day's close. The warning message actually confirms the fix is working as intended—it's alerting me that today's data hasn't arrived yet since the market hasn't opened, so returning 0.0 is correct. The core issue was that stale data was being mislabeled as today's information, which is now resolved. For a more complete solution, I could either add a pre-market mode that disables the index return gate when data is missing, or integrate real-time index data from a source like Eastmoney to use during market hours instead of relying on the previous day's close.","thinkingSignature":"bfcfe0918ac4a3330ac540bb6db08c4e7f31720ad83d3f2e9267d53cb5cc250b"},{"type":"text","text":"修复生效。`latest_index_return_pct()` 现在会检测数据陈旧并返回 0.0 + 告警，而不是误用昨天的 -2.31%。\n\n**补充一个更完整的修复**——在盘前门控层面加入\"数据未就绪\"的降级逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_518m1fx0oe07_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '195,250p' /Us