{"type":"message","id":"6731f09a","parentId":"e39e056c","timestamp":"2026-03-20T03:48:00.337Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. Each of the three paper accounts has `initial_cash: 1000000.0` (100万). The total across all three is 300万.\n\nBut the `daily_add_budget: 1200000.0` is the sum of per-ticket budgets:\n- Defensive: 80,000 (8% of 1M)\n- Balanced: 120,000 (12% of 1M)\n- Aggressive: 180,000 (18% of 1M)\n\nWait, but the USER says \"我的预算为什么是120万\" - maybe they're referring to the total across all three accounts being 120万? Or maybe they're saying the daily_add_budget is wrong at 120万?\n\n\nActually, re-reading their message: \"我的预算为什么是120万？我从来没给过这个口径\" - they explicitly state they've never set a 120万 budget. Looking at the USER.md, it says \"模拟盘口径：按 100 万可用资金计算\", but the system appears to be using 120万 as the daily_add_budget instead. I need to figure out where that 120万 figure is actually coming from.\n\nThe daily_add_budget calculation seems to be the sum of per-ticket budgets across all three paper accounts (80k + 120k + 180k = 1200k), which doesn't align with the 100万 standard the user is referring to. The core issue is that the system is using the combined total across multiple accounts rather than respecting the per-account 100万 limit the user intended. the default available cash for the single-account live config is 100万. But for the paper (simulated) trading which has 3 accounts, the budgets are summed.\n\nSo the fix depends on what the user wants:\n1. If they want each paper account to have 100万 → already correct (each has initial_cash=1000000)\n2. If they want the TOTAL daily_add_budget to be 100万 → need to fix the calculation\n3. If they want the per-account budgets to change → need to update the configs\n\nGiven the user says \"120万\" is wrong and \"从来没给过这个口径\", they seem to want the budget to NOT be 120万. The most likely interpretation is that the user expects the system to use 100万 as the base, not 120万.\n\nBut here's what's strange - the MEMORY says 模拟盘口径 is 100万, yet the actual paper accounts show each one initialized with exactly 100万. If that's true, where is the 120万 coming from? Let me trace through the report files more carefully to find where this discrepancy originates.","thinkingSignature":"a2e866a62343cba796c8fd1779b752bb400117e7a3ce6d0e981feb4f6c8f8769"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wxsuar4skhga_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd = json.load(open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/investment_research_paper_execution_summary_20260319.json'))\nfor p in d.get('profiles', []):\n    print(p.get('slot_label'), p.get('profile_slug'))\n    stats = p.get('stats', {})\n    print('  daily_add_budget:', stats.get('daily_add_budget'))\n    print('  per_buy_budget:', stats.get('per_buy_budget'))\n    account = p.get('account', {})\n    print('  initial_cash:', account.get('initial_cash'), 'nav:', account.get('nav'), 'cash:', account.get('cash'))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":75949,"output":746,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773978461124}}
