{"type":"message","id":"8e456ff0","parentId":"05ec4f54","timestamp":"2026-03-20T03:48:10.338Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the 03-19 data clearly:\n- 盘一 (defensive): daily_add_budget = 200,000 (80,000 per ticket × some slots)\n- 盘二 (balanced): daily_add_budget = 400,000 (120,000 per ticket × some slots)\n- 盘三 (aggressive): daily_add_budget = 600,000 (180,000 per ticket × some slots)\n- Total = 1,200,000 = 120万\n\nSo the 120万 is NOT the available cash, it's the DAILY ADD BUDGET (total budget for new buys across all 3 accounts in one day).\n\n\nEach account is initialized with 100万 in cash, and the daily_add_budget represents how much of that can be deployed each day. Looking at the 20260320 data, all three accounts show daily_add_budget = 0 because hard_stop is triggered, which halts new buys across the board.\n\nThe 120万 figure the user is questioning was from the 03-19 snapshot before the halt was triggered, and it represents the configured daily add budget across all three paper accounts combined. Now I need to trace where this 120万 configuration actually comes from in the prepare_paper_orders_v1 script.","thinkingSignature":"4641ed8d6b108041d7c1180532a29acd369aadf1af2b0942d4411d037fc3732d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3rbbacrycpzi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"daily_add_budget\\|per_buy_budget\\|buy_budget_slots\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py 2>/dev/null | head -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":76860,"output":358,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102095,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773978480438}}
