{"type":"message","id":"1423a76e","parentId":"d5a5a3d2","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:32:05.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that when breadth is unavailable and gate_action is neither \"halt\" nor \"cautious\" (the `else` branch), it keeps the base runtime's mode and only adds to gate_reasons. This means if the base runtime mode is `normal`, it stays `normal` even when breadth is unavailable.\n\nThis is the bug. When `gate_action` is not \"halt\" but breadth is unavailable, the system should still go to `cautious` at minimum, not keep `normal`.\n\nLet me look at the gate_action determination.","thinkingSignature":"2976adc772f0fd0cae15b34b2e75572a29b1a5aed6c5a41b883b3fc8f9ad7fff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nr9ag952rhbj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"gate_action\\|breadth.*available\\|intraday_gate\\|get_intraday\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_intraday_risk_recheck.py | head -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92839,"output":204,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117920,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981119360}}
