{"type":"message","id":"c309b070","parentId":"6c527330","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:33:03.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The intraday gate is disabled because it's \"非交易时段\" (non-trading hours). It's 12:29 PM which is between 11:30-13:00 (lunch break). So the intraday gate is not enabled, meaning our fix in `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py` doesn't even get triggered.\n\nThe core issue is:\n1. `event_watch` shows halt because its paper execution system independently evaluates breadth and halts when it's low (0.092)\n2. `runtime_risk_state` shows normal because:\n   a. The intraday gate is disabled during lunch break (non-trading hours)\n   b. The base runtime doesn't include breadth as a halt condition\n\nSo the mismatch stems from the event_watch's paper execution evaluating market breadth independently and halting when it's low, while the runtime risk state never even gets to evaluate breadth because the gate is disabled during the lunch break period.\n\nI need to fix this by ensuring that when the intraday gate is disabled, the runtime still incorporates market breadth as a halt factor, so both systems are evaluating the same conditions consistently.","thinkingSignature":"496d25e511f6cbfdae24a9ebdeb91c8ad963f16a31c704ec096d40307259caad"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4k7yyqht846q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"intraday_gate\\|enabled.*False\\|非交易\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/intraday_market_gate.py 2>/dev/null | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93885,"output":315,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119077,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981176079}}
