{"type":"message","id":"1dc0472f","parentId":"9b16eac1","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:33:13.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The intraday gate is disabled during the lunch break (非交易时段). During this time, the system doesn't evaluate market breadth and the runtime stays in `normal` mode. But the `event_watch` system does evaluate breadth and halts because 0.092 is very low.\n\nThe fix should be: even when the intraday gate is disabled, if the `runtime_metrics.market_breadth` is below the hard_stop threshold, the system should halt rather than stay in `normal` mode. The `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py` should handle this case.\n\nBut the issue is: when is `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py` called? Is it only during intraday? Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"d2cc54cf9283cb696959613ce049b8c570d646afe80c5ee4f346300d80e4621c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1duiy1e9gwep_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"run_intraday_risk\\|intraday.*risk\\|risk.*recheck\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/heartbeat-quant-ops.md 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93387,"output":233,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118497,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981183813}}
