{"type":"message","id":"854b432f","parentId":"8f4dcb30","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:33:30.235Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` is written by `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py`. The tester reads this file and compares with `event_watch`. \n\nThe issue is that during lunch break (12:29 PM), the intraday gate is disabled, and the `run_intraday_risk_recheck` doesn't apply the breadth halt. But `event_watch` has the paper execution's halt (from earlier when the market was open).\n\nThe core issue is that `runtime_risk_state` is meant to be the authoritative real-time state, but it doesn't reflect the breadth halt during non-trading hours when the intraday gate is disabled.\n\n\nThe solution is to ensure `runtime_risk_state` always evaluates breadth halt conditions regardless of the intraday gate status, so the state remains consistent even during lunch breaks. Let me check how `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py` writes to the state file to understand where to apply this fix.","thinkingSignature":"4efb0a61ea2ad1f2c54e7e1f9273eebef06b15503c57a6f30969a6fa1c7bba6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5yeib503nbo3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"runtime_risk_state_latest\\|write\\|dump\\|to_json\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_intraday_risk_recheck.py | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91301,"output":288,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116466,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981198123}}
