{"type":"message","id":"43124923","parentId":"4e96c658","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:35:08.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `paper_defensive_execution_brief` shows `market_breadth = 0.377` (which is healthy). So where does the 0.092 in `event_watch.current.paper_execution_status.market_breadth` come from?\n\nThe issue is that `event_watch` is generated by `run_investment_research_event_watch.py` and it applies an overlay from `runtime_risk_state`. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the event_watch code in `run_investment_research_event_watch.py`:\n```python\napply_runtime_overlay(summary)\n```\n\nThis patches the summary with data from `runtime_risk_state_latest`. But `runtime_risk_state_latest` has `runtime_metrics.market_breadth = 0.377`.","thinkingSignature":"f69e6ea16e6b0e8f044f456e183f61d22e6125b151ad6ee304ffc8d2865babcc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xuorjqu7zfzi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"apply_runtime_overlay\\|paper_execution_status\\|market_breadth.*0.092\\|0.092\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py 2>/dev/null | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92610,"output":256,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117743,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981297286}}
