{"type":"message","id":"d787ab8a","parentId":"5f840524","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:35:17.255Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p2o1ojbgl6q6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def apply_runtime_overlay(summary: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    date_tag = str(summary.get(\"strategy_report_date_tag\") or summary.get(\"paper_date_tag\") or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\"))\n    runtime_obj, report_obj = load_runtime_overlay(date_tag)\n    latest_runtime = runtime_obj.get(\"latest_runtime\") or {}\n\n    if str(runtime_obj.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") == date_tag and latest_runtime:\n        summary[\"risk_off\"] = bool(latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"))\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.update(\n            {\n                \"source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest\",\n                \"mode\": latest_runtime.get(\"mode\"),\n                \"risk_off\": latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"),\n                \"hard_stop\": latest_runtime.get(\"hard_stop\"),\n                \"halt_new_buy\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\"),\n                \"halt_reason\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_reason\"),\n                \"market_breadth\": latest_runtime.get(\"market_breadth\"),\n                \"gate_reasons\": latest_runtime.get(\"gate_reasons\") or [],\n                \"allowed_to_open_new_positions\": not bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n                \"runtime_state_path\": str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST),\n            }\n        )\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n        source_paths = dict(summary.get(\"source_paths\") or {})\n        source_paths[\"runtime_risk_state_json\"] = str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST)\n        summary[\"source_paths\"] = source_paths\n\n    trade_date_text = str(report_obj.get(\"trade_date\") or \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    if trade_date_text == date_tag and report_obj:\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.setdefault(\"source\", \"strategy_report\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\") is not None:\n            pe[\"mode\"] = report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_off\") is not None:\n            pe[\"risk_off\"] = report_obj.get(\"risk_off\")\n            summary[\"risk_off\"] = bool(report_obj.get(\"risk_off\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\") is not None:\n            pe[\"hard_stop\"] = report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\") is not None:\n            pe[\"halt_new_buy\"] = report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\")\n            pe[\"allowed_to_open_new_positions\"] = not bool(report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\"):\n            pe[\"halt_reason\"] = report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\")\n        if \"market_breadth\" in report_obj:\n            pe[\"market_breadth\"] = report_obj.get(\"market_breadth\")\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n    return summary\n\n\ndef should_reset_baseline(prev: dict[str, Any] | None, cur: dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[bool, str]:\n    if not prev:\n        return False, \"\"\n\n    prev_dt = parse_dt(prev.get(\"generated_at\"))\n    if prev_dt != datetime.min and (datetime.now() - prev_dt).days >= 2:\n        return True, \"previous_state_stale\"\n\n    prev_source_paths = prev.get(\"source_paths\", {}) or {}\n    old_holdings = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"app_holdings_csv\") or \"\")\n    old_live_report = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"live_system_report\") or \"\")\n    if \"ths_app_holdings_\" in old_holdings or \"live_system_v1\" in old_live_report:\n        return True, \"previous_state_old_execution_regime\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"def apply_runtime_overlay(summary: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    date_tag = str(summary.get(\"strategy_report_date_tag\") or summary.get(\"paper_date_tag\") or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\"))\n    runtime_obj, report_obj = load_runtime_overlay(date_tag)\n    latest_runtime = runtime_obj.get(\"latest_runtime\") or {}\n\n    if str(runtime_obj.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") == date_tag and latest_runtime:\n        summary[\"risk_off\"] = bool(latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"))\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.update(\n            {\n                \"source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest\",\n                \"mode\": latest_runtime.get(\"mode\"),\n                \"risk_off\": latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\"),\n                \"hard_stop\": latest_runtime.get(\"hard_stop\"),\n                \"halt_new_buy\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\"),\n                \"halt_reason\": latest_runtime.get(\"halt_reason\"),\n                \"market_breadth\": latest_runtime.get(\"market_breadth\"),\n                \"gate_reasons\": latest_runtime.get(\"gate_reasons\") or [],\n                \"allowed_to_open_new_positions\": not bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n                \"runtime_state_path\": str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST),\n            }\n        )\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n        source_paths = dict(summary.get(\"source_paths\") or {})\n        source_paths[\"runtime_risk_state_json\"] = str(RUNTIME_STATE_LATEST)\n        summary[\"source_paths\"] = source_paths\n\n    trade_date_text = str(report_obj.get(\"trade_date\") or \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    if trade_date_text == date_tag and report_obj:\n        pe = dict(summary.get(\"paper_execution_status\") or {})\n        pe.setdefault(\"source\", \"strategy_report\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\") is not None:\n            pe[\"mode\"] = report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"risk_off\") is not None:\n            pe[\"risk_off\"] = report_obj.get(\"risk_off\")\n            summary[\"risk_off\"] = bool(report_obj.get(\"risk_off\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\") is not None:\n            pe[\"hard_stop\"] = report_obj.get(\"hard_stop\")\n        if report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\") is not None:\n            pe[\"halt_new_buy\"] = report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\")\n            pe[\"allowed_to_open_new_positions\"] = not bool(report_obj.get(\"halt_new_buy\"))\n        if report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\"):\n            pe[\"halt_reason\"] = report_obj.get(\"trigger_reason\")\n        if \"market_breadth\" in report_obj:\n            pe[\"market_breadth\"] = report_obj.get(\"market_breadth\")\n        summary[\"paper_execution_status\"] = pe\n    return summary\n\n\ndef should_reset_baseline(prev: dict[str, Any] | None, cur: dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[bool, str]:\n    if not prev:\n        return False, \"\"\n\n    prev_dt = parse_dt(prev.get(\"generated_at\"))\n    if prev_dt != datetime.min and (datetime.now() - prev_dt).days >= 2:\n        return True, \"previous_state_stale\"\n\n    prev_source_paths = prev.get(\"source_paths\", {}) or {}\n    old_holdings = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"app_holdings_csv\") or \"\")\n    old_live_report = str(prev_source_paths.get(\"live_system_report\") or \"\")\n    if \"ths_app_holdings_\" in old_holdings or \"live_system_v1\" in old_live_report:\n        return True, \"previous_state_old_execution_regime\"","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773981317238}}
{"type":"message","id":"a057b366","parentId":"d787ab8a","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:35:30.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! The `apply_runtime_overlay` function patches `paper_execution_status` with data from `runtime_risk_state_latest`. It sets `market_breadth` to `latest_runtime.get(\"market_breadth\")`. But `latest_runtime.market_breadth` is only set when the intraday gate is applied and breadth is available. During non-trading hours, it remains as the base_runtime's market_breadth.\n\nLet me check what `latest_runtime.market_breadth` actually is right now in the runtime_risk_state_latest.json.\n\nActually, from the earlier check, I see that `runtime_metrics.market_breadth = 0.377` and `latest_runtime.market_breadth` is not explicitly set (it's part of the `latest_runtime` object).\n\n\nSo when `apply_runtime_overlay` runs, it pulls `latest_runtime.market_breadth` which is `None` since it was never populated. This means `pe.market_breadth` gets set to `None`, but then something overwrites it back to `0.092`. The issue must be that the `paper_execution_status` object is getting rebuilt somewhere else after the overlay is applied.","thinkingSignature":"f15555ae863b3daafa17d8d7c129375ca670fa009ba9503eb1c32794817bdbe6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xm5jx6fufy3i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\new = json.load(open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/investment_research_event_watch_20260320.json'))\nprint('event_watch.status:', ew.get('status'))\nprint('event_watch.generated_at:', ew.get('generated_at'))\nprint()\ncur = ew.get('current', {})\nprint('current keys:', list(cur.keys()))\nprint()\nprint('paper_execution_status.market_breadth:', cur.get('paper_execution_status', {}).get('market_breadth'))\nprint('current.market_breadth:', cur.get('market_breadth'))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"