{"type":"message","id":"b690973d","parentId":"4e1d57b3","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:35:43.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `paper_execution_status.market_breadth = 0.092` is coming from the `paper_execution_summary` object, not from `runtime_risk_state`. The `apply_runtime_overlay` function patches some fields, but the original `market_breadth` from the paper execution summary remains as `0.092`.\n\nThe `event_watch` is generated by `run_investment_research_event_watch.py`, which:\n1. Loads the `paper_execution_summary` \n2. Applies `apply_runtime_overlay` which patches some fields from `runtime_risk_state`\n3. But the `market_breadth` in `paper_execution_status` (0.092) is from the paper execution itself\n\n\n4. Now I need to trace where this `market_breadth = 0.092` originates in the `paper_execution_summary`.\n\nThe `paper_execution_summary` is built by `build_paper_execution_snapshot()` in `investment_research_paper_bridge.py`, which pulls data from each profile's `stats` object. Looking at the execution brief, the halt reason shows `market_breadth(0.0920) <= 0.2500`, so I need to find where this market_breadth value is being set in the stats dictionary.","thinkingSignature":"95b4bbc840f180cbad52a0405aa0514b4ab3219a0bb30215412d8597e0c3bdc9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z9j6n9lgwtf8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"market_breadth.*0.092\\|0.092\\|market_breadth\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v __pycache__ | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90739,"output":373,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981330869}}
