{"type":"message","id":"a5ff68ce","parentId":"8d7ed010","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:35:55.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` uses `runtime_metrics.get(\"market_breadth\")` which comes from `runtime_risk_state`. But the `paper_execution_summary` shows `market_breadth = 0.092`. Let me check the actual data flow.\n\nWait, let me look at the `paper_execution_summary` file directly. The `paper_execution_status` in `event_watch` comes from `paper_execution_summary.execution_status`. Let me check what that shows.","thinkingSignature":"09bf549256c07a623df65153d895b9e60fe747a1ee1bc59b1dcabaeb30bda550"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fpcnj4pyx07u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd = json.load(open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/investment_research_paper_execution_summary_20260320.json'))\npe = d.get('execution_status', {})\nprint('paper_execution_summary.execution_status.market_breadth:', pe.get('market_breadth'))\nprint('source:', pe.get('source'))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90787,"output":227,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115891,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981343663}}
