{"type":"message","id":"f43e2540","parentId":"881142c8","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:37:22.029Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `base_runtime.mode = normal` because the `runtime_metrics.market_breadth = 0.377 > 0.35`. The base runtime correctly evaluates breadth as healthy now.\n\nThe fundamental issue is that the morning `event_watch` halt was based on `market_breadth = 0.092` (pre-market scan), but the current runtime shows `market_breadth = 0.377` (intraday calculation that refreshed during the trading session).\n\nThese are two different breadth measures:\n1. Pre-market breadth (0.092) - computed before market open, checks how many stocks are above their moving averages at market open\n\n\n2. Intraday breadth (0.377) - computed during trading hours, different methodology\n\nThe morning halt was correct given the pre-market breadth reading, but as the session progressed the intraday breadth improved. The tester is flagging a stale `event_watch` state - it still shows `halt` because it was built during morning precheck when breadth was 0.092, while the runtime has since refreshed to 0.377 and shows `normal` mode. This is a real inconsistency that needs addressing, so I should regenerate the `event_watch` with current data.","thinkingSignature":"c2ff6e61f9988743870f0b0488c953bcc9bf6bd0b217b40020088857c921baa1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2xu85n0v3qof_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/run_investment_research_event_watch.py 2>&1 | tail -5","yieldMs":30000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":89286,"output":333,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114496,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773981430266}}
