{"type":"message","id":"50ae390c","parentId":"6dac331b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:33:44.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it!\n\n**Root cause of the bug:**\n\nThe `apply_runtime_overlay` function has TWO overlays:\n1. **First** (runtime_risk_state overlay): Sets `pe[\"mode\"] = \"cautious\"` ✅\n2. **Second** (report_obj overlay): Sets `pe[\"mode\"] = report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\") = \"normal\"` → **OVERWRITES the cautious mode!**So the second block is the culprit. It overwrites the `cautious` mode from runtime_risk_state with the `normal` mode from the paper_execution_summary report.The fix: The second block should only update fields that are NOT already set by the first block, OR it should use `pe.setdefault(\"mode\", report_obj.get(\"risk_mode\"))` instead of directly assigning.\n\nActually, looking at the second block more carefully - it's meant to be a fallback from `strategy_report` when `runtime_risk_state` doesn't have data. \n\nBut the real issue is that it's unconditionally overwriting everything. The cleanest solution would be to use `pe.setdefault()` for each field instead of direct assignment, preserving whatever the first overlay set. The `risk_mode` field is probably stale from the morning report and shouldn't override the intraday caution state anyway.\n\nNow I need to check the Tester ALERT about the market breadth mismatch between runtime (0.2716) and the report (0.3769) to see if that's the same root cause.\n\nThe Tester compares `runtime_metrics.market_breadth` against `report.get(\"market_breadth\")`, so I should verify which metric it's actually pulling.","thinkingSignature":"dae7f6ef7ce75b4231810f9b99a453893006ce323d4184bc035f636550892d6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xwbu82j1apew_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '38,55p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_tester_scheduled_guard.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"