{"type":"message","id":"d1f04f94","parentId":"174a5c37","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:27:26.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand:\n\n- The CSV has data for 20260318 (close=8096.5948, pct_chg=0.9568%) and 20260319 (close=7909.2343, pct_chg=-2.3141%)\n- But the file's LAST UPDATE was at 03/19 18:10 (after market close for 03/19)\n- So when `morning_scan.py` ran on 03/19 morning, it read data from 03/18 (last available data at that time), showing ZZ2000 was UP 0.96% on 03/18- That's why the execution brief says `zz2000_ret_pct: 0.96%` - this was the LATEST available return at the time of running (the 03/18 return)\n\n\n- The `intraday_risk_recheck` correctly detected the halt with market breadth at 0.649 and index return showing positive 0.96%, but then the rollback plan claimed halt_new_buy was true while the brief's brief shows no such thing. I need to trace what happened at 03/19 22:54 when the final recheck was recorded.","thinkingSignature":"ae6f85c2e24facaba40c25c3418a2de110099915b3fdeedaf54725db4fea048d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wl2jnx8tnhso_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nREPORT = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports')\nd = json.load(open(REPORT / 'intraday_risk_recheck_20260319_2254.json'))\nlr = d.get('latest_runtime', {})\nrm = d.get('runtime_metrics', {})\nprint('=== 20260319 22:54 final intraday ===')\nprint('mode:', lr.get('mode'))\nprint('halt_new_buy:', lr.get('halt_new_buy'))\nprint('halt_reason:', lr.get('halt_reason'))\nprint('market_breadth:', rm.get('market_breadth'))\nprint('index_ret_pct:', rm.get('index_ret_pct'))\nprint('gate_reasons:', lr.get('gate_reasons'))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99798,"output":469,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":1251