{"type":"message","id":"d0936719","parentId":"3afba30e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:51:25.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `size_orders()` DOES check `runtime.halt_new_buy` at line 1540. If `halt_new_buy=True`, it should set `risk_gate = \"blocked\"` and `suggest_qty = 0`.\n\nBut the 20260319 orders show `risk_gate=pass` for 002151 and 002173! So the `halt_new_buy` was NOT set when `size_orders` was called for 20260319.\n\nThis means that in the INTRADAY halt scenario (during the day when the intraday gate was checked), the `runtime.halt_new_buy` was set, BUT it wasn't being used by the paper execution pipeline because the paper pipeline runs separately from the intraday recheck.\n \nI see the issue now—the paper orders pipeline doesn't actually read from the same runtime object that gets updated by the intraday gate. It's pulling from a separate runtime state file. Let me trace through how the paper orders pipeline initializes and retrieves its runtime information to understand where the disconnect is.","thinkingSignature":"9c4377a759541d57f714d2c53efc3c3ac48e7ada087c8a98cf05e21e9e96be75"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j5czxd1rxnet_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '50,100p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98347,"output":283,"cacheRead":24877,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773993070073}}
{"type":"message","id":"fabed28d","parentId":"d0936719","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:51:25.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j5czxd1rxnet_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MERGED_SIGNALS_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"merged\"\nDEFAULT_RISK_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"risk\" / \"configs\" / \"default_risk_config.json\"\n\n\ndef parse_float(value: Any, default: float = 0.0) -> float:\n    try:\n        return float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip())\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_date_tag(value: str) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip()\n    if re.fullmatch(r\"\\d{8}\", text):\n        return text\n    if re.fullmatch(r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\", text):\n        return text.replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    raise ValueError(f\"无效日期: {value}\")\n\n\ndef parse_optional_date_tag(value: Any) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip()\n    if not text:\n        return \"\"\n    return parse_date_tag(text)\n\n\ndef tag_to_iso(tag: str) -> str:\n    return f\"{tag[0:4]}-{tag[4:6]}-{tag[6:8]}\"\n\n\ndef resolve_path(path_like: str) -> Path:\n    path = Path(str(path_like))\n    if path.is_absolute():\n        return path\n    return (PROJECT_ROOT / path).resolve()\n\n\ndef latest_file_in_dir(directory: Path, pattern: str) -> Path:\n    files = sorted(directory.glob(pattern))\n    if not files:\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"未找到文件: {directory / pattern}\")\n    return files[-1]\n\n\ndef extract_date_tag(path: Path) -> str:\n    match = re.search(r\"(\\d{8})\", path.name)\n    return match.group(1) if match else datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n\n\ndef resolve_merged_signals_path(date_tag: str, merged_signals_arg: str = \"\") -> Path:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5,"aggregated":"MERGED_SIGNALS_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"merged\"\nDEFAULT_RISK_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"risk\" / \"configs\" / \"default_risk_config.json\"\n\n\